feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104kmz1665702706437.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kmz1665702706437.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/kmz1665702706437.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"kmz1665702706437\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      lock level\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set the Sybase transaction isolation level.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__topic_d59669e1_d59670e1_d59671e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__p_d59672e1_d59673e1_d59674e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SYS$SYB_PARAMS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">= lock level 0</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code> | <code class=\"ph codeph\">3</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__section_qvj_zqw_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1041768e69\">Arguments</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__ul_d24_zqw_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__li_d26663e1_d26664e1_d26665e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__p_d59678e1_d59679e1_d59680e1\">0—dirty reads. These do not acquire any locks,\n                  and are not recommended. With this level, it is possible that the result set of a\n                  level 0 scan changes while the scan is in progress.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__li_d26666e1_d26667e1_d26668e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__p_d59681e1_d59682e1_d59683e1\">1—allows shared read locks on data. This is the\n                  standard Sybase lock level. (Default)</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__li_d26669e1_d26670e1_d26671e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"kmz1665702706437__p_d59684e1_d59685e1_d59686e1\">3—the Sybase SQL Server applies a holdlock to\n                  all select and readtext operations in a transaction until the end of that\n                  transaction. This lock isolation level can cause problems in a multiuser\n                  environment, because locks are held longer than normally.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529287\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529287\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "lock level Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 lock level Set the Sybase transaction isolation level. SYS$SYB_PARAMS = lock level 0 | 1 | 3 Arguments 0—dirty reads. These do not acquire any locks, and are not recommended. With this level, it is possible that the result set of a level 0 scan changes while the scan is in progress. 1—allows shared read locks on data. This is the standard Sybase lock level. (Default) 3—the Sybase SQL Server applies a holdlock to all select and readtext operations in a transaction until the end of that transaction. This lock isolation level can cause problems in a multiuser environment, because locks are held longer than normally. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}